WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.882 --> 00:00:03.210
(upbeat music)

00:00:03.210 --> 00:00:06.770
- So a number of years ago I
developed my first invention

00:00:06.770 --> 00:00:08.800
to treat bone density.

00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:13.130
It became very apparent that
humans are seven times stronger

00:00:13.130 --> 00:00:15.100
than they think they are.

00:00:15.100 --> 00:00:19.580
And the reason is, we have
vastly different capabilities

00:00:19.580 --> 00:00:22.530
of producing power in different positions

00:00:22.530 --> 00:00:23.960
of our biomechanics.

00:00:23.960 --> 00:00:27.093
And this wasn't really
documented or understood before.

00:00:28.411 --> 00:00:30.590
So what X3 does

00:00:30.590 --> 00:00:33.360
is allows us to train

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:37.160
with appropriate forces
in different positions,

00:00:37.160 --> 00:00:41.370
so it uses extremely heavy latex banding

00:00:41.370 --> 00:00:45.510
to deliver the proper forces
in the proper positions.

00:00:45.510 --> 00:00:49.080
So I'm holding much more force,

00:00:49.080 --> 00:00:51.450
maybe five to seven times a force here,

00:00:51.450 --> 00:00:53.080
in this stronger position,

00:00:53.080 --> 00:00:55.623
than I am in the weaker position.

00:00:57.130 --> 00:01:01.240
The success of X3 has also

00:01:01.240 --> 00:01:06.190
driven the success and the
prevalence of band training.

00:01:06.190 --> 00:01:10.380
The problem with training
with a band by itself is

00:01:10.380 --> 00:01:11.830
you have two options,

00:01:11.830 --> 00:01:16.830
either the band is appropriately
forced for rehab training,

00:01:17.280 --> 00:01:20.220
or what we really see is rehab

00:01:20.220 --> 00:01:23.460
banding being repurposed for fitness,

00:01:23.460 --> 00:01:26.590
but nobody's gonna get
stronger with 20 pounds.

00:01:26.590 --> 00:01:31.590
When individuals try to use
heavier banding without a bar,

00:01:33.060 --> 00:01:34.960
this happens to the wrist.

00:01:34.960 --> 00:01:36.810
The wrist gets twisted,

00:01:36.810 --> 00:01:39.140
and these are some of the
smallest bones in the body,

00:01:39.140 --> 00:01:41.840
and they can get damaged very easily.

00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:46.030
So there is a reason why we interface

00:01:46.030 --> 00:01:48.860
our feet with flat surfaces so well,

00:01:48.860 --> 00:01:51.610
there is a reason that our hand interfaces

00:01:51.610 --> 00:01:53.190
with a bar so well,

00:01:53.190 --> 00:01:55.883
because that's what
keeps our wrist neutral.

00:01:56.932 --> 00:01:59.210
So we all get to train with
a higher amount of weight

00:01:59.210 --> 00:02:00.380
than we normally would,

00:02:00.380 --> 00:02:03.590
with more repetitions
than we normally would,

00:02:03.590 --> 00:02:06.000
all while protecting joints,

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:11.000
so that we get a more complete
and more powerful stimulus

00:02:11.120 --> 00:02:12.503
to trigger muscle growth.

